 How to create and insert a new element into the DOM

To add a new element to a webpage using JavaScript, you normally follow three steps:
First, create the element using document.createElement().
Second, add content to it (like text or HTML).
Third, insert it somewhere in the page using methods like appendChild() or append().
For example, if you want to add a new paragraph to the body:
Create a paragraph
Set its text
Append it to document.body
That’s it. JavaScript builds the element first in memory, then attaches it to the actual page.



