 What is Event Bubbling?

Event bubbling is how events move inside the DOM.
When you click on an element (for example, a button inside a div), the event doesn’t just stay on the button. It first runs on the button, then moves upward to its parent, then to the parent’s parent, and so on — until it reaches the document.

So, the event travels from the innermost element outward.
This is why sometimes clicking a child element also triggers the parent’s event listener.



