 What is Event Delegation? Why is it useful?

Event delegation is a smart way to handle events.
Instead of adding separate event listeners to many child elements, you attach one event listener to their parent. Then, inside that parent listener, you check which child triggered the event.
This works because of event bubbling.
Why it’s useful:
Improves performance (less listeners in memory)
Cleaner code
Works even if new elements are added dynamically later
It’s very helpful in projects like job lists, dashboards, or dynamic cards.



